      "id": "PopularPost100590",
      "post_content": "The fact that Lightning Rift changes all cycled cards into direct damage for just one additional mana is what made RW Rift/Slide decks viable up through early Mirrodin Standard. It transforms [Renewed Faith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Renewed Faith) into a mini cantrip Lightning Helix, adds more damage to a cycled [Slice and Dice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Slice and Dice), and burns while fetching a plains through a landcycled [Eternal Dragon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eternal Dragon). Alas, the insane speed of Post-Darksteel Standard with Ravager Affinity, Tooth and Nail, and Tribal Clamp/Bidding decks dominating the meta left rift/slide smoldering in their wake. Nonetheless, this is a very powerful and somewhat underrated enabler that saw continued support in Extended for some time after Onslaught rotated from Standard. For me, it's the epitome of what made cycling great back in Onslaught Standard and is every bit as important and powerful as its more popular white cousin.",
      "posted_by": "Digit",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost100590\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">The fact that Lightning Rift changes all cycled cards into direct damage for just one additional mana is what made RW Rift/Slide decks viable up through early Mirrodin Standard. It transforms <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Renewed Faith\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Renewed Faith\">Renewed Faith</a> into a mini cantrip Lightning Helix, adds more damage to a cycled <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Slice and Dice\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Slice and Dice\">Slice and Dice</a>, and burns while fetching a plains through a landcycled <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Eternal Dragon\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eternal Dragon\">Eternal Dragon</a>.  Alas, the insane speed of Post-Darksteel Standard with Ravager Affinity, Tooth and Nail, and Tribal Clamp/Bidding decks dominating the meta left rift/slide smoldering in their wake.  Nonetheless, this is a very powerful and somewhat underrated enabler that saw continued support in Extended for some time after Onslaught rotated from Standard.  For me, it's the epitome of what made cycling great back in Onslaught Standard and is every bit as important and powerful as its more popular white cousin.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '100590'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<di